1. n. One of the mythical race dwelling in regions of gloom described in the writings of Homer. 

-adj. Dark, dismal, gloomy.


'''Cimmerians''', are an ancient mythological people chronicled in Homeric poems which are 
supposed to inhabit the far west where the sun never shone. Name is also 
given by Herodotus to historical people living on the Black Sea, who migrated 
to Asia Minor 7th cent., and settled in Lydia; name still retained in Crimea. 
Phrase 'Cimmerian darkness' is used for utter, intense darkness.